@node usage "cha_bsr.guide/Usage"

    cha_bsr should be started from the Shell.

    cha_bsr FILE S=SCREEN/K SX=SENDSYSEX/S CC=SENDCONTROLLERS/S M=MIDICHANNEL/K/N

    FILE
        The name of a BassStation Rack patch file to
        load.  The original default patch (found in the
        empty slots on a new BassStation Rack) is used
        if FILE is not specified.
 |      Actually the default patch is preset 00.

    SCREEN/K
        The name of a public screen to open on, for
        example "OCTAMED".  If SCREEN is not specified
        cha_bsr opens on the default public screen
        (usually the Workbench screen).

    SENDSYSEX/S
        If specified, a sysex message is sent to the
        BassStation every time a slider is moved or a
        file is loaded.  This might be problematic if
        there is lots of other MIDI stuff going on at
        the same time.
        If not specified, sysex messages are only sent
        when the "Dump" button is pressed.
        Note that sysex messages are always received.

    SENDCONTROLLERS/S
        If specified, MIDI control change messages are
        sent for some envelope and filter settings each
        time a slider is moved.  If SENDSYSEX is also
        specified, sysex is not sent for the parameters
        which can be controlled by controllers.
        This setting does not affect the extra
        controllers window - these always send control
        change messages.  Note also that controller
        messages are always received.

    MIDICHANNEL/N/K
        The MIDI channel to use for the controller
        messages, in the range 1..16.  This is not
        needed for the sysex messages which are not
        channel specific.
        If not specified, the default channel is 16
        (which is where I keep my BassStation).


    I have a Shell alias "bsr" (with the abbreviated
    arguments):

    Alias bsr Run somepath/cha_bsr s OCTAMED sx cc m 16

@endnode

@node windows "cha_bsr.guide/Windows"

    Main window
        The buttons above the bar open windows to edit
        BassStation parameters.  For full details of those
        parameters see the BassStation manual.

        Note that all sliders display hexadecimal values, if
        you really really want a decimal version I might be
        able to be persuaded to make one.

        Save
            Save the current patch to a file.

        Load
            Load a patch file.

        Dump
            Dump the current patch to MIDI.


    Other windows
        See the BassStation manual for details of the
        parameters.  The manual is available online from
        Novation's website.


    EXTRA window
        Extra MIDI commands can be sent from here to see the
        effect of various patch settings.  These sliders do not
        affect the stored patch in any way.

@endnode

@node presets "cha_bsr.guide/Presets"

    I have included the BassStation Rack presets in the preset/
    drawer, along with a file listing the names of the presets
    (as found on the back of the MIDI implementation chart).
    In the future this file might be used by other tools to
    make selecting patches in music programs less painful.

    @{" preset/names.txt " link preset/names.txt/main}

@endnode

@node bugs "cha_bsr.guide/Bugs"

    There aren't any serious bugs (I hope, if you find one
    please report it so I can fix it!), but there are a few
    things I'm not sure about.  If you have any suggestions
    for improvements, or extra information on the points
    below, tell me.

    OSC2 semitone control.
        In use this appears to take values 00-0C, but in the
        sysex dump it takes values 00-FF.  I guess it must
        jump between the actual settings at certain fixed
        levels, but I don't know those exact levels so I've
        left the slider controlling the full range.

    Parameters with continuous controllers.
        The filter and envelope settings can be adjusted with
        control change MIDI messages, which can take values
        00-7F.  But in the sysex dump they take values 00-FF,
        so cha_bsr sends the actual value divided by two as a
        continuous controller.  This might be wrong.

    Filter modulation depth.
        This parameter can be modified by controller messages,
        but there is only one controller to control both ENV2
        and LFO modulation.  The one actually controlled
        depends on the filter modulation source switch (I
        guess), but this is complicated by the fact that that
        switch can only be controlled by sysex.  For this
        reason neither of the filter modulation sliders send
        this continuous controller.

    Multiple BassStation Racks.
        The sysex dump format doesn't include any channel
        information, so patches will be recognised by all
        connected BassStations Racks.  However, the controller
        messages that modify some parameters do have an
        associated channel.  The best thing to do with multiple
        BassStations is to either have them on separate MIDI
        interfaces so they don't interact at all, or to have
        them chained in polyphonic mode (read the manual for
        details).

    Sysex dump format.
        I wrote to Novation asking for details of the sysex
        format ages ago, but rewriting this patch editor I
        found a few inaccuracies (namely: the envelope
        triggering setting is stored differently to what the
        docs say).  cha_bsr handles this setting like my
        BassStation Rack does, not like the docs say.

    OctaMED MIDI message file format.
        No documentation exists for this, so I worked it out
        from hex dumps of different files.  Some files may not
        be recognised, if you find one send it to me.
 |      OctaMED support not yet implemented.

@endnode

